The police yesterday arraigned a 60-year-old man, Martins Anyakoro, in a Badagry Magistratesâ€™ Court for allegedly posing as a Naval officer. Anyakoro was charged with two counts of impersonation and breach of the peace. Prosecuting Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) Clement Okuoimose said the defendant committed the offence on June 13 at 6:30pm at the Naval Base FOB Badagry, Lagos. Okuoimose said the defendant paraded himself as a Navy Captain at the base. The defendant, he added, also conducted himself in a manner likely to cause a breach of the peace by entering the base and harassing officers on duty. Magistrate Olalekan Aka-Bashorun granted Anyakoro N200,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. He adjourned till July 10.